1 (25) Publicly available information. – Information that is lawfully made readily
2 available to the general public through federal, State, or local government
3 records or widely distributed media and a controller has a reasonable basis to
4 believe a consumer has lawfully made readily available to the general public.
5 (26) Sale of personal data. – The exchange or transfer of personal data for monetary
6 or other valuable consideration by the controller to a third party. "Sale of
7 personal data" does not include any of the following:
8 a. The disclosure of personal data to a processor that processes the
9 personal data on behalf of the controller where limited to the purpose
10 of the processing.
11 b. The disclosure of personal data to a third party for purposes of
12 providing a product or service affirmatively requested by the
13 consumer.
14 c. The disclosure or transfer of personal data to an affiliate of the
15 controller.
16 d. The disclosure of personal data where the consumer directs the
17 controller to disclose the personal data or intentionally uses the
18 controller to interact with a third party.
19 e. The disclosure of personal data that the consumer intentionally made
20 available to the general public via a channel of mass media and did not
21 restrict to a specific audience.
22 f. The disclosure or transfer of personal data to a third party as an asset
23 that is part of a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, or other similar
24 transaction in which the third party assumes control of all or part of
25 the controller's assets, or a proposed merger, acquisition, bankruptcy,
26 or other similar transaction in which the third party assumes control of
27 all or part of the controller's assets.
28 (27) Sensitive data. – Personal data that includes any of the following:
29 a. Data revealing racial or ethnic origin, religious beliefs, mental or
30 physical health condition or diagnosis (including pregnancy), sex life,
31 sexual orientation, status as transgender or nonbinary, national origin,
32 citizenship status, or immigration status.
33 b. Genetic or biometric data.
34 c. Personal data of a known child.
35 d. Precise geolocation data.
36 (28) Sexual assault. – Any sexually violent offense as defined in G.S. 14-208.6 or
37 any equivalent provision in the laws of any other state; the United States; any
38 territory, district, or subdivision of the United States; or any foreign
39 jurisdiction.
40 (29) Stalking. – The offense defined in G.S. 14-277.3A or any equivalent provision
41 in the laws of any other state; the United States; any territory, district, or
42 subdivision of the United States; or any foreign jurisdiction.
43 (30) Targeted advertising. – Displaying advertisements to a consumer where the
44 advertisement is selected based on personal data obtained or inferred from that
45 consumer's activities over time and across nonaffiliated internet websites or
46 online applications to predict the consumer's preferences or interests.
47 "Targeted advertising" does not include any of the following:
48 a. Advertisements based on activities within a controller's own internet
49 websites or online applications.
50 b. Advertisements based on the context of a consumer's current search
51 query, visit to an internet website, or online application.
